tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows significantly elevated creatinine, indicating impaired renal function, and dyslipidemia with high total and LDL cholesterol and low HDL cholesterol, increasing cardiovascular risk. Other parameters, including glucose, electrolytes, liver enzymes, and proteins, are within normal limits. Renal function and lipid profile require clinical attention and further evaluation.
